# Phase 9: CLI Tool

**Phase:** 9 of 12
**Status:** Not Started
**Depends on:** Phase 3 (Auth -- GitHub OAuth tokens, `withAuth` middleware for API routes), Phase 6 (Dashboard API -- project listing, deployment triggers, env var CRUD), Phase 8 (Caching, Streaming & Rollback -- build log streaming via WebSocket/SSE, rollback endpoint)
**Blocks:** None (final user-facing feature phase)

---

## Goal

The `gblockparty` CLI tool is fully functional. Users can authenticate via GitHub OAuth, link a local directory to a project, trigger deployments, manage environment variables, view build logs, and rollback to previous deployments -- all from the terminal.

After this phase:
- `gblockparty login` opens the browser, authenticates via GitHub OAuth, and stores an auth token at `~/.gblockparty/config.json`
- `gblockparty link` fetches the user's projects from the API and saves the selected project ID to `.gblockparty/config.json` in the current directory
- `gblockparty deploy` triggers a deployment, streams build logs in real-time, and prints the deployment URL on success
- `gblockparty env pull` downloads env vars to `.env.local` and `gblockparty env push` uploads them
- `gblockparty logs` shows build logs for the latest deployment with `-f` for real-time streaming
- `gblockparty rollback` lists recent deployments and rolls back to a selected one
- Server-side CLI API routes at `/api/cli/deploy` and `/api/cli/env/:projectId` are implemented and secured with Bearer token auth

---

## Architecture Context

```
Developer Machine                   Dashboard (Next.js 15)              GitHub
  |                                       |                              |
  | $ gblockparty login                   |                              |
  |-- open browser ---------------------->|-- /api/auth/github --------->|
  |                                       |<-- OAuth callback -----------|
  |<-- local server receives token -------|                              |
  |-- save to ~/.gblockparty/config.json  |                              |
  |                                       |                              |
  | $ gblockparty link                    |                              |
  |-- GET /api/projects ----------------->|                              |
  |<-- [{ id, name, slug }] -------------|                              |
  |-- (user selects project)              |                              |
  |-- save to .gblockparty/config.json    |                              |
  |                                       |                              |
  | $ gblockparty deploy --prod           |                              |
  |-- POST /api/cli/deploy -------------->|                              |
  |   { projectId, branch, commitSha,     |-- queue build                |
  |     production: true }                |-- start build pipeline       |
  |<-- SSE/WS: build log stream ---------|                              |
  |<-- { url, deploymentId } ------------|                              |
  |                                       |                              |
  | $ gblockparty env pull                |                              |
  |-- GET /api/cli/env/:projectId ------->|                              |
  |   ?scope=production                   |                              |
  |<-- { vars: [{ key, value }] } -------|                              |
  |-- write to .env.local                 |                              |
  |                                       |                              |
  | $ gblockparty env push                |                              |
  |-- POST /api/cli/env/:projectId ------>|                              |
  |   { scope, vars: [{ key, value }] }  |-- upsert env_vars table      |
  |<-- { updated: N } -------------------|                              |
  |                                       |                              |
  | $ gblockparty logs -f                 |                              |
  |-- GET /api/projects/:id/deployments ->|                              |
  |-- WS /api/.../logs/stream ----------->|                              |
  |<-- streamed log lines ----------------|                              |
  |                                       |                              |
  | $ gblockparty rollback                |                              |
  |-- GET /api/projects/:id/deployments ->|                              |
  |<-- [{ id, commitSha, status, ... }] --|                              |
  |-- (user selects deployment)           |                              |
  |-- POST /api/.../rollback ------------>|-- re-deploy old image        |
  |<-- { ok, deploymentId } -------------|                              |
```

